    {
      "citation_path": "us-wa/statute/82/82.87/82.87.160",
      "metadata": {
        "chapter": "82.87",
        "heading": "Credit \u2014 Sale or exchange of long-term capital assets \u2014 Transfer from general fund",
        "kind": "section",
        "notes": [
          "Reviser's note: The tax preference enacted in 2025 c 409 s 3 expires January 1, 2037, pursuant to the automatic expiration date established in RCW 82.32.805 (1)(a).",
          "Effective date \u2014 2025 c 409 ss 3, 4, 8, 10, and 15: \"Sections 3, 4, 8, 10, and 15 of this act take effect January 1, 2026.\" [ 2025 c 409 s 16 .]",
          "Application \u2014 2025 c 409: \"(1) The expiration of RCW 82.04.4497 provided in RCW 82.04.4497 (5) does not affect: (a) Any existing right acquired or liability or obligation including, but not limited to: (i) A taxpayer's liability for tax, penalty, or interest; (ii) A taxpayer's ability to claim a credit under RCW 82.04.4497 earned from sales or exchanges that occurred before the expiration of RCW 82.04.4497 ; or (iii) A taxpayer's ability to claim relief from tax, penalty, or interest; (b) Any rule or order adopted under RCW 82.04.4497 ; or (c) Any proceeding instituted under RCW 82.04.4497 . (2) For purposes of this section, \"liability for tax\" means that the obligation for payment of a tax has been incurred by a taxpayer, regardless of when the tax is payable or whether the amount of tax due has been established.\" [ 2025 c 409 s 2 .]"
        ],
        "parent_citation_path": "us-wa/statute/82/82.87",
        "references_to": [
